com.github.arachnidium.core.settings.supported

Enum ESupportedDrivers

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ESupportedDrivers>
      • com.github.arachnidium.core.settings.supported.ESupportedDrivers
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<ESupportedDrivers>

    public enum ESupportedDrivers
extends Enum<ESupportedDrivers>
    There is information about supported WebDriver implementors
    - FirefoxDriver
    - ChromeDriver
    - InternetExplorerDriver
    - SafariDriver
    - PhantomJSDriver
    - RemoteWebDriver
    - AndroidDriver
    - IOSDriver

    - is browser only
    - is for mobile applications only
    Additional info:
    - default Capabilities
    - information about DriverService
    - can WebDriver be started remotely?
    - is WebDriver require URL of remotely or locally started
    server. (SeleniumServer or Appium Node.js server (see http://appium.io/slate/en/master/?ruby#appium-design)

      • REMOTE

        public static final ESupportedDrivers REMOTE
        Required WebDriver implementor: RemoteWebDriver

        Default Capabilities: DesiredCapabilities.firefox()()

        Starts: locally and remotely. When it is started locally SeleniumServer is started it the same time.
        browser only
        If it needs to be launched remotely it requires URL of the host where Appium node server (if ExtendedDesiredCapabilities.androidChrome() or ExtendedDesiredCapabilities.iosSafari() are used) or SeleniumServer are started, e.g. http://127.0.0.1:4723/wd/hub (local host). Information about Appium node server please find here:
        http://appium.io/getting-started.html
        Information about SeleniumServer: https://code.google.com/p/selenium/wiki/Grid2

        DriverService: optionally. If it is run locally with DesiredCapabilities.chrome(), DesiredCapabilities.internetExplorer() or DesiredCapabilities.phantomjs() then ChromeDriverService, InternetExplorerDriverService or PhantomJSDriverService should be set up respectively

      • ANDROID_APP

        public static final ESupportedDrivers ANDROID_APP
        Required WebDriver implementor: AndroidDriver

        Default Capabilities: empty. They should be defined explicitly. Here is an example:
          "deviceName":{
            "value":"desired device name e.g. Android Emulator, NEXUS and so on"
          },
          "app":{
            "value":"absolute path to desired *.apk file"
          }

        It is enough for the successful starting. Also see MobileCapabilityType
        DriverService: none

        Starts: remotely. It requires URL of the host where Appium node server is started, e.g. http://127.0.0.1:4723/wd/hub (local host). Please find information here:
        http://appium.io/getting-started.html
        mobile apps only

      • IOS_APP

        public static final ESupportedDrivers IOS_APP
        Required WebDriver implementor: IOSDriver

        Default Capabilities: empty. They should be defined explicitly. Here is an example:
          "platformVersion":{
            "value":"7.1"
          },
          "deviceName":{
            "value":"desired device name e.g. iPhone Simulator"
          },
          "app":{
            "value":"absolute path to desired *.app"
          }

        It is enough for the successful starting. Also see MobileCapabilityType
        DriverService: none

        Starts: remotely. It requires URL of the host where Appium node server is started, e.g. http://127.0.0.1:4723/wd/hub (local host). Please find information here:
        http://appium.io/getting-started.html
        mobile apps only
